      "sc:author": "Oleksii Nikolaienko",
      "sc:citation": {
        "@id": "https://doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/btab586"
      },
      "sc:description": "ramr is an R package for detection of epimutations (i.e., infrequent aberrant DNA methylation events) in large data sets obtained by methylation profiling using array or high-throughput methylation sequencing. In addition, package provides functions to visualize found aberrantly methylated regions (AMRs), to generate sets of all possible regions to be used as reference sets for enrichment analysis, and to generate biologically relevant test data sets for performance evaluation of AMR/DMR search algorithms.",
